All Classes

Class Description
AuthorizingRequestHandler
Base class for requests that require an auth token to perform the request.
AuthToken
Class that represents authentication tokens
AuthTokenDao
This class provides an interface to interact with Authentication Tokens in the database
ClearHandler
Handlers requests to clear all data from the database
ClearResult
Class that holds the results of a clear request
ClearService
Class that preforms the service of clearing the database
DaoObject
This abstract object forms the base of all the DAO objects.
DataAccessException
Exception to be thrown when an error occurs accessing the database
Database
A class that contains the connection to the database to be used by the data access objects
DataRetrievalRequest
Base class for the Request objects that hold request data for data retrieval services
DataRetrieveService
Base class for all services that retrieve data from the database (GET methods).
DateTime
This class provides functionality of getting timestamps and for converting timestamps to a number for easy comparision
Event
Class that represents event data in the database
EventAllResult
Class that holds the result of a request to receive all events associated with a user
EventDao
Class that provides access to the events in the database
EventHandler
Handles requests to get event data from the database
EventRequest
Class to hold the data necessary to process an event retrieval request
EventResult
Class that holds the result of an event retrieval request
EventService
Class that preforms the service of searching for an event(s) in the database
FileHandler
This class handles any request that is not implemented by another handler and interprets it as a request for a file to be displayed.
FillHandler
Handles requests to generate a specified number of generations of person and event data for a given user
FillRequest
Class that holds the data necessary to process a fill service request
FillResult
Class that holds the results of a Fill request
FillService
Class that preforms the service of filling in the database with person and event data for a specified user
LoadHandler
Handles request to load data into the database
LoadRequest
Class that holds the data necessary to process a load service request
LoadResult
Class that holds the result data of a load request
LoadService
Class that preforms the service of loading given data into the server
Location
Class used to hold location information to be used in event generation.
LocationData
Class to hold locations to be used in event generation
LoginHandler
Handles requests to login a user that has been registered in the database and returns a new auth token.
LoginRequest
Class that stores data to process a login service request
LoginResult
This class represents the login result message of the login service.
LoginService
Preforms the service of logging a user back into the program
ModelObject
This abstract class serves as the foundation of each model object.
NameData
Class to hold names to be used when generating new person objects
Person
Class that represents person data in the database
PersonAllResult
Class that holds the result of a request to receive all persons associated with a user
PersonDao
Class that allows access to person data in the database
PersonHandler
Handles requests to get person data from the database
PersonRequest
Class to hold the data necessary to process a person retrieval request
PersonResult
Class that holds the result of a request to receive a person associated with a user
PersonService
Preforms the service of retrieving person(s) data from the database
PostRequestHandler
Base class for Handlers that handle a post request.
RegisterHandler
Handles requests to register a new user to the database and returns a new auth token.
RegisterRequest
This class receives the data from the message body of a request to register a new user.
RegisterResult
This class represents the register result message of the register service.
RegisterService
This class carries out the services required to register a new user to the database.
RequestHandler
This class implements the base functionality of each of the server's handlers.
Result
This is the base class of the result objects.
Server
Server that receives requests to access, change and get data from the database from a client.
Service
Base class of all service classes.
User
User object to hold data to be put into the database, or hold data retrieved from the database.
UserDao
This class provides a way to read and write user data in the database.
